# CQ4.3 (COMPETENCY_QUESTIONS.md concept 4): "Which representations or
# warranties have NO disclosed exception at all (the unqualified,
# full-strength clauses)?" -- the negation of CQ4.1.
#
# Added in the 2026-07-18 L5-push Round 3 pass. A first draft used
# `FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?scheduleItem ... ma:qualifiesClause ?clause }`, which
# a real repro (scratch consumer, not this pack's fixtures) proved this
# engine evaluates WITHOUT correlating ?clause to the outer binding -- it
# silently returned every Representation/Warranty, qualified or not,
# identical to omitting the FILTER entirely. Rewritten to `MINUS`, which the
# same repro confirmed correlates correctly. This is a real, disclosed
# engine limitation (this engine's SPARQL FILTER NOT EXISTS is not usable
# for correlated negation), not a query-authoring mistake to fix by hand
# next time -- see also self-monitoring-pack's disclosed sh:sparql/ORDER BY
# limitations in the same engine.
#
# Verified live (post-fix) against fixtures/case.ttl (1 row:
# rep-target-financial-statements -- the ONE Representation with no
# ma:qualifiesClause pointing at it; warranty-target-no-material-litigation
# is correctly excluded because Schedule 3.14(b) qualifies it) and
# fixtures/case-2.ttl (0 rows -- its only Representation,
# rep-target-environmental-compliance, IS qualified by Schedule 4.02, so the
# unqualified set there is empty) via the scratch consumer at
# /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-sac-ggen/70ac08c7-8655-49c4-baa2-018bc441bb4c/
# scratchpad/l5-round3-ma-case-study-pack/.

PREFIX fibo-fnd-agr-ctr: <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FND/Agreements/Contracts/>
PREFIX ma: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/ma-case-study#>

SELECT ?clause WHERE {
  { ?clause a fibo-fnd-agr-ctr:Representation . }
  UNION
  { ?clause a fibo-fnd-agr-ctr:Warranty . }
  MINUS {
    ?scheduleItem a ma:DisclosureScheduleItem ;
                  ma:qualifiesClause ?clause .
  }
}
